From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Lusoris <lusoris@pm.me>
Date: Mon, 11 May 2026 23:30:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] libvmaf: add libvmaf_metal filter (zero-copy IOSurface import)

Introduces a dedicated `libvmaf_metal` FFmpeg filter that consumes
VideoToolbox-decoded frames (`AVFrame->format == AV_PIX_FMT_VIDEOTOOLBOX`,
`AVFrame->data[3] -> CVPixelBufferRef`), pulls the IOSurface backing
the buffer via `CVPixelBufferGetIOSurface`, and routes it through
`vmaf_metal_picture_import` / `vmaf_metal_read_imported_pictures` for
a zero-copy import path without the `hwdownload,format=nv12` round-trip
the regular `libvmaf` filter forces.

Pairs with the C-API surfaces in
libvmaf/include/libvmaf/libvmaf_metal.h:
  - vmaf_metal_state_init_external (adopts FFmpeg's MTLDevice so
    source IOSurface handles are valid on libvmaf's compute device —
    same-device requirement symmetric to ADR-0184 / Vulkan)
  - vmaf_metal_import_state
  - vmaf_metal_picture_import (per-plane IOSurface bridge)
  - vmaf_metal_wait_compute (per-frame synchronisation barrier)
  - vmaf_metal_read_imported_pictures (route to scoring pipeline)

Closes T8-IOS (Metal IOSurface zero-copy import) in the fork backlog.
Companion to 0012-libvmaf-wire-metal-backend-selector.patch (which adds
the `metal_device` option to the regular libvmaf filter); together the
two patches give users:

  * libvmaf=metal_device=N    — software AVFrame input + Metal compute
  * libvmaf_metal=...         — VideoToolbox hwdec + zero-copy import

Status (T8-IOS implementation, ADR-0423): the
`vmaf_metal_state_init_external` / `vmaf_metal_picture_import` /
`vmaf_metal_wait_compute` / `vmaf_metal_read_imported_pictures`
entry points ship as a working IOSurface → VmafPicture memcpy
import on Apple-Family-7+ hosts. The filter passes
`device=0, command_queue=0` so libvmaf falls back to
`MTLCreateSystemDefaultDevice` until FFmpeg exposes an
`AVMetalDeviceContext`. See
docs/adr/0423-metal-iosurface-import-scaffold.md.

Patch is on top of 0001-0012 (post-metal-backend-selector baseline).

---
 configure                |  3 +
 libavfilter/Makefile     |  1 +
 libavfilter/allfilters.c |  1 +
 libavfilter/vf_libvmaf.c | 269 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 4 files changed, 274 insertions(+)

